47:03.254 --> 47:05.387
If we talkin' fair,

47:05.423 --> 47:06.656
How 'bout a little
somethin' for the man

47:06.791 --> 47:07.924
That introduced you two?

47:07.926 --> 47:09.391
Shut up!

47:10.261 --> 47:11.861
This is you free and clear.

47:12.931 --> 47:19.335
(soft dramatic music)

47:19.470 --> 47:21.570
This is me
renegotiating my terms.

47:22.941 --> 47:28.344
(soft dramatic music)

47:28.479 --> 47:29.912
Sticks!

47:32.150 --> 47:33.949
Fix mr. Massey
and I a drink.

47:33.985 --> 47:39.955
(soft dramatic music)

47:39.991 --> 47:44.160
♪

47:44.295 --> 47:45.727
Hey junior!

47:46.631 --> 47:48.831
Hey, you makin'
a big mistake.

47:48.966 --> 47:50.366
Look, you shoulda got
out from under queenie

47:50.435 --> 47:51.834
While you had the chance.

47:51.969 --> 47:53.568
My debt is clear.

47:53.605 --> 47:54.770
This is a new arrangement.

47:54.772 --> 47:56.839
Look, I get the appeal.

47:56.974 --> 47:58.441
Queenie's smart,

47:58.443 --> 47:59.842
Powerful,

47:59.977 --> 48:01.710
Sexy as all hell-

48:01.779 --> 48:03.178
Nigga that ain't your cousin?

48:03.180 --> 48:04.981
That mean I
don't got eyes?

48:04.983 --> 48:07.383
Look, don't let that
do-good shit fool you, man.

48:07.518 --> 48:09.451
That woman don't care
about nobody but herself.

48:09.487 --> 48:10.386
The second you
become a problem-

48:10.521 --> 48:11.586
Bobby, I ain't you

48:11.623 --> 48:12.922
So there ain't gonna be
no motherfuckin' problem.

48:12.991 --> 48:13.990
Thank you very much.

48:13.992 --> 48:15.725
All I'm saying is,

48:15.860 --> 48:18.728
It's not too late to start
thinking about a exit plan.

48:24.335 --> 48:26.234
You sure you know
what you're doing?

48:26.271 --> 48:28.604
That shit use to drive the
soldiers crazy in the war.

48:28.673 --> 48:32.641
Well folks are still going
crazy for it over here.

48:32.677 --> 48:36.278
And it's a whole lot easier
to smuggle than booze.

48:36.347 --> 48:38.280
You know my granny
always used to say,

48:39.550 --> 48:41.817
(in patois) who cyah
hear mus' feel.

48:41.886 --> 48:42.952
What that mean?

48:42.954 --> 48:44.586
<i> Miss queenie's</i>
<i> already beat your ass</i>

48:44.656 --> 48:45.620
For going behind her back.

48:45.657 --> 48:47.223
And there you is.

48:48.426 --> 48:51.394
Look, I'm just trying
to be somebody, junior.

48:51.529 --> 48:53.128
Ain't that what we all want?

48:53.164 --> 48:58.300
(tense dramatic music)

48:58.336 --> 48:59.902
I got a train
to catch.

49:01.506 --> 49:03.005
Stay outta trouble, hm.

49:03.007 --> 49:04.573
Get you some pooch
or something.

49:04.709 --> 49:10.646
(dramatic blues music)

49:10.715 --> 49:20.656
♪

49:20.791 --> 49:30.733
♪

49:30.802 --> 49:40.208
♪

49:40.244 --> 49:42.745
You wanna know who
your real friends are?

49:42.747 --> 49:44.814
See who turns up when
life knocks you down.

49:46.951 --> 49:48.684
Think this is
'cause of my meeting?

49:50.455 --> 49:51.554
All I know,

49:51.689 --> 49:54.690
This garden was the beginning
of a new chapter here.

49:54.825 --> 49:56.425
A way to stop depending
on the railroad

49:56.461 --> 49:57.893
To keep our doors open.

49:58.963 --> 50:00.429
Well, we'll find a way.

50:00.465 --> 50:03.232
Our folks in saint are
pull together people.

50:04.969 --> 50:06.902
I've seen it time
and time again.

50:07.772 --> 50:09.438
You might be
right about that.

50:13.511 --> 50:14.643
<i> What's this about?</i>

50:14.645 --> 50:15.778
This?

50:15.847 --> 50:17.713
A token of support on behalf
of the welfare committee.

50:19.183 --> 50:20.982
You mean on behalf
of the railroad.

50:21.019 --> 50:23.853
Stanley:
<i> The welfare committee serves</i>
<i> porters and their families.</i>

50:23.855 --> 50:25.187
The company wants
you all to know,

50:25.189 --> 50:26.622
We're here for
the community.

50:26.691 --> 50:28.457
So quickly?

50:28.526 --> 50:30.992
I mean, the smoke hasn't
even cleared yet

50:31.029 --> 50:32.595
And here you are, stanley.

50:32.730 --> 50:34.596
We should get these
to the cold room.

50:34.598 --> 50:37.266
Would hate to see fine folks
cooking up spoilt chicken.

50:38.536 --> 50:39.802
This way.

50:43.041 --> 50:46.542
Stanley, are you
responsible for this?

50:47.812 --> 50:49.545
Hand to the most high,

50:49.680 --> 50:51.613
I don't know
who did this.

50:52.683 --> 50:54.149
<i> But maybe you should</i>
<i> be more careful</i>

50:54.285 --> 50:56.085
<i> Who you invite to</i>
<i> your meetings.</i>

50:56.220 --> 50:58.987
(gentle piano music)

51:06.230 --> 51:11.500
(dramatic upbeat music)

51:11.536 --> 51:14.503
(train rumbling)

51:14.539 --> 51:18.307
(dramatic upbeat music)

51:18.376 --> 51:21.777
(indistinct announcement)

51:24.048 --> 51:25.381
Junior:
<i> Save the lecture,</i>

51:25.383 --> 51:26.816
I already spoke to queenie and
everything's gonna be alright.

51:26.951 --> 51:29.184
Junior, we have a rat
reporting to edwards.

51:30.521 --> 51:31.553
<i> It's one of our own.</i>

51:31.589 --> 51:33.455
You know which one
of us they after?

51:33.457 --> 51:35.424
What makes you think
it's only one?

51:35.426 --> 51:41.330
(dramatic suspenseful music)

51:41.465 --> 51:45.267
♪
